---
By: Sivananda
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 264
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Illusions
---
Worldly enjoyments are fleeting like the flashes of lightning. Human life
is ephemeral like the bubble. The vigor of youth is short-lived. All these
are illusory in this world.
